Class Database

  • java.lang.Object
    • Database

  • public class Database
extends java.lang.Object
    This class will hold all of the known Junction points. A Junction can be merely a Junction in which roads meet, or there could be a Restaurant or Farm at that point.
    Author:
    Craig Lombardo

    • Constructor Detail

      • Database

        public Database(java.lang.String conns,
                java.lang.String farms,
                java.lang.String rests)
        The constructor method creates a new empty database.
        Parameters:
        conns - An input file serving as the connectivity list, all entries should be on their own line in the form of:
        <conn1> - <conn2> <distance>
        farms - An input file serving as the list of Farms in the area, all entries should be on their own line and should be in the form of:
        farm <node name> - <ingredient1> <cost> <ingredient2> <cost> ...
        rests - An input file serving as the list of Restaurants in the area, all entries should be on their own line and should be in the form of:
        restaurant <number>
